      <abstract obkms_id="37536748-a38b-4dfc-801a-21823c0a1b32" obkms_process="TRUE">
        <label>Abstract</label>
        <p><italic><tp:taxon-name obkms_id="edcb059f-63ef-42f1-b45f-346dbb034378" obkms_process="TRUE"><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Spiradiclis</tp:taxon-name-part><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">pengshuiensis</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Bo Pan &amp; R. J. Wang (<tp:taxon-name obkms_id="c3ac9d3b-1ea6-41e6-b989-a421c07ac03b" obkms_process="TRUE"><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="family">Rubiaceae</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name>) is described as a new species from Chongqing in SW China. It is morphologically compared with <italic><tp:taxon-name obkms_id="c5974f96-3734-4634-93e0-35e7b41bd02a" obkms_process="TRUE"><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Spiradiclis</tp:taxon-name-part><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">pauciflora</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> L. Wu &amp; Q. R. Liu because of their similarities in habit, pubescent surface, small leaf laminas and subglobose capsules. Its conservation status is evaluated as “VU” according to the IUCN categories and criteria.</p>
      </abstract>
